  "prompt": "What are the best Engineering Colleges in Punjab?",
  "response": "Punjab, India, is home to several prestigious engineering colleges. Some of the top engineering institutions in Punjab include:\n\n1. **Indian Institute of Technology (IIT) Ropar**  \n   - One of the premier engineering institutes in India, IIT Ropar is known for its excellent faculty, research facilities, and academic rigor.\n\n2. **Thapar Institute of Engineering and Technology (TIET), Patiala**  \n   - A top-ranked private engineering college in Punjab, Thapar University is known for its strong focus on engineering disciplines and placements.\n\n3. **Punjab Engineering College (PEC), Chandigarh**  \n   - PEC is one of the oldest and most reputed engineering colleges in India, offering quality education and research opportunities.\n\n4. **Dr. B.R. Ambedkar National Institute of Technology (NIT Jalandhar)**  \n   - NIT Jalandhar is a well-known government engineering institute offering a range of undergraduate and postgraduate programs.\n\n5. **Lovely Professional University (LPU), Phagwara**  \n   - LPU is one of the largest private universities in India, offering a wide range of engineering programs and state-of-the-art facilities.\n\n6. **Chandigarh University (CU), Mohali**  \n   - Known for its modern infrastructure and industry-oriented curriculum, CU is a popular choice for engineering aspirants.\n\n7. **Guru Nanak Dev Engineering College (GNDEC), Ludhiana**  \n   - A reputed government engineering college, GNDEC is known for its strong academic programs and placement record.\n\n8. **DAV Institute of Engineering and Technology (DAVIET), Jalandhar**  \n   - A well-known private engineering college with a focus on innovation and practical learning.\n\n9. **Rayat Bahra University, Mohali**  \n   - Offers a variety of engineering programs and is known for its modern facilities and industry collaborations.\n\n10. **Sant Longowal Institute of Engineering and Technology (SLIET), Longowal**  \n   - A government-funded institute offering specialized engineering and technology programs.\n\nThese institutions are highly regarded for their academic excellence, infrastructure, and placement opportunities. When choosing a college, consider factors such as accreditation, faculty, industry collaborations, and placement records.",
